---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About · Gerard Agba"
  description="I build n8n workflows that automate DTC finance operations. Free episodes on YouTube, paid installs for brands $2-15M ARR."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-16">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-[color:var(--color-accent)] mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-tight tracking-tight">
      I automate the parts of DTC finance that shouldn&rsquo;t be a human job.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert mt-10 max-w-none text-[color:var(--color-fg)] space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Hi, I&rsquo;m Gerard. I build n8n workflows that recover money DTC brands are
        leaking through misbilled marketplace fees, manual reconciliation,
        chargeback paperwork, and a hundred other half-baked finance processes.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most $2&ndash;15M brands run finance with <strong>three full-time roles
        worth of glue work</strong>: pulling CSVs, matching payouts, chasing
        disputed charges, formatting month-end reports. None of it should be
        a person&rsquo;s job in 2026.
      </p>

      <p>
        This channel is the public version of what I do for clients. Every
        episode breaks down one real, expensive finance problem and ships
        the workflow that fixes it. Free. JSON included. No paywall.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">What I&rsquo;ve built</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
        <li>Multi-channel reconciliation (Shopify + Amazon + Faire + PayPal + Klarna)</li>
        <li>FBA fee audit + reimbursement claim packets</li>
        <li>Chargeback evidence builder (auto-PDF with shipping + order history)</li>
        <li>Cash-flow runway forecaster pulling from Mercury + Stripe</li>
        <li>50+ more workflows in the <a href="/templates" class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">templates library</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">How to work with me</h2>
      <p>
        If you want a workflow installed on your actual data, I do that.
        Fixed-scope, fixed-price, done in 2 weeks. See <a href="/work-with-me" class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">work with me</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
